description.narrative: Amidst continued escalation of insecurity, killings of Polio workers compounded by Covid-19 pandemic the program timely procured and delivered vaccines to support 9.9m under-five children with Polio vaccination. Three out of nine planned National Immunization Days (NID) were implemented. To date four Wild Polio Virus(WPV) and 45 Vaccine Derived Polio (VDPV) have been reported. The increasing immunity gap has led to three of the reported cases originating from non-polio hotspot locations due to inaccessibility. New political leadership permitted vaccination for all children in all locations through both house to house (197 districts) and Mosque to Mosque (202 districts) modalities. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:12/01/2022
